<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN243-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. toṭittalai viḻuttaṇṭiṉār pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN243">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>iṉiniṉain tirakka mākiṉṟu tiṇimaṇaṟ</l>
<l>ceyvuṟu pāvaikkuk koypūt taiit</l>
<l>taṇkaya māṭu makaḷiroṭu kaipiṇaintu</l>
<l>taḻuvuvaḻit taḻīit tūṅkuvaḻit tūṅki</l>
<l>maṟaiyeṉa laṟiyā māyami lāyamō</l>
<l>ṭuyarciṉai marutat tuṟaiyuṟat tāḻntu</l>
<l>nīrnaṇip paṭikō ṭēṟic cīrmikak</l>
<l>karaiyavar maruḷat tiraiyakam pitira</l>
<l>neṭunīrk kuṭṭattut tuṭumeṉap pāyntu</l>
<l>kuḷittumaṇaṟ koṇṭa kallā viḷamai</l>
<l>yaḷitō tāṉē yāṇṭuṇṭu kollō</l>
<l>toṭittalai viḻuttaṇ ṭūṉṟi naṭukkuṟ</l>
<l>ṟirumiṭai miṭainta cilacoṟ</l>
<l>perumū tāḷarē mākiya vemakkē.</l></lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Thinking now it has become regret. (1a-c)</l>
<l>Untaught youth when (10cd)</l>
<l>entwining hands with girls that play in the cool pond, (3)</l>
<l>knitting flowers plucked for dolls that have motion, in the firm sand (1d-2)</l>
<l>embracing the way one embraces, swaying the way one sways, (4)</l>
<l>together with companions without deception who do not know of saying “secret”, (5)</l>
<l>dangling from the high-branched Myrobalan tree to have the ghat, (6)</l>
<l>rising on mounds [of sand] settling near the water, (7)</l>
<l>jumping with a splash into the expanse of long water, (9)</l>
<l>so that spray came up from the waves to confound those on the shore mightily, (7d-8)</l>
<l>	[we] took the sand after bathing, (10)</l>
<l>– pitiful is it. Where is it, (11)</l>
<l>for us who have become great old men (14)</l>
<l>of few words posed at long intervals, (13)</l>
<l>trembling, leaning on excellent sticks with ringed heads? (12)</l>
</lg>


